The United States has announced its decision to join the Christchurch Call to Action, a global initiative aimed at eliminating terrorist and violent extremist content online. This move highlights the country's commitment to countering the use of the internet for radicalization and recruitment by terrorists and violent extremists. The United States supports the emphasis on human rights and the rule of law in the Christchurch Call, including the protection of freedom of expression. By joining the initiative, the United States affirms that it will not infringe upon the freedoms of speech, association, or privacy protected by the First Amendment to the U.S. Constitution. The country will participate in the Christchurch Call Second Anniversary virtual summit on May 14.